# Release Workflow

## Branching Strategy

- `main` — production releases only
- `staging/<nwsl-team>` — feature staging branches (e.g., `staging/courage`)
- `feat/<name>` — feature branches targeting staging
- `fix/<name>` — bug fix branches targeting main (for hotfixes)

## Feature Development

1. Create `feat/<name>` branch off the active `staging/<team>` branch
2. Open PR targeting `staging/<team>`
3. Merge to staging when approved

## Release Flow

1. When staging is ready, bump the minor version in `package.json`
2. Update `CHANGELOG.md` with the version number, team name, and date
3. Merge `staging/<team>` to `main`
4. Create a GitHub Release (which also creates the tag): `gh release create v<version> --target main --title "v<version> — <Team> Release" --notes-file CHANGELOG.md`

## Hotfixes (direct to main)

1. Create `fix/<name>` branch off `main`
2. Bump the patch version in `package.json`
3. Add changelog entry for the patch
4. Open PR targeting `main`
5. After merge, create a GitHub Release: `gh release create v<version> --target main --title "v<version>" --notes "..."`

## Version Bumping

- **Minor** (1.x.0): feature releases from staging (no breaking changes)
- **Patch** (1.1.x): bug fixes direct to main
- **Major** (x.0.0): breaking changes (schema migrations, removed features)
- Version is auto-injected at build time via `__APP_VERSION__` from `package.json`
